ra-oral Radiography device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-IVOCT">IVOCT</a></td><td>Tomographie par cohérence optique intravasculaire</td><td>An acquisition device, process or method that performs intravascular optical coherence tomography</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-IVUS">IVUS</a></td><td>Ultrasonore intravasculaire</td><td>Intravascular Ultrasound device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-KER">KER</a></td><td>Kératométrie</td><td>Keratometry device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-LEN">LEN</a></td><td>Lensométrie</td><td>Lensometry device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-LS">LS</a></td><td>Scan laser</td><td>Laser surface scan device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-MG">MG</a></td><td>Mammographie</td><td>Mammography device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-MR">MR</a></td><td>Résonance magnétique</td><td>Magnetic Resonance device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-NM">NM</a></td><td>Médecine nucléaire</td><td>Nuclear Medicine device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OAM">OAM</a></td><td>Mesures axiales ophtalmiques</td><td>Measurements of the axial length of the eye, which are done by various devices</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OCT">OCT</a></td><td>Tomographie à cohérence optique</td><td>Modality device that uses an interferometric, non-invasive optical tomographic technique to image 2D slices and 3D volumes of tissue using visible and near visible frequencies</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OP">OP</a></td><td>Photographique ophtalmique</td><td>Ophthalmic photography modality</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OPM">OPM</a></td><td>Cartographie ophtalmique</td><td>Modality device that measures corneal topography, corneal or retinal thickness, and other similar parameters that are typically displayed as maps</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OPT">OPT</a></td><td>Tomographie ophtalmique</td><td>Tomography of the eye acquired by a modality that is based on light and optical principles. Tomography based on other principles, such as ultrasound, is excluded</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OPTBSV">OPTBSV</a></td><td>Tomographie ophtalmique B-scan analyse de volume</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OPTENF">OPTENF</a></td><td>Tomographie ophtalmique en face</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OPV">OPV</a></td><td>Champ visuel ophtalmique</td><td>Modality device that measures visual fields and perform visual perimetry</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-OSS">OSS</a></td><td>Scanner optique de surface</td><td>An acquisition device, process or method that performs optical surface scanning</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-POS">POS</a></td><td>Détecteur de position</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-PT">PT</a></td><td>TEP : Tomographie par émission de positons</td><td>Positron emission tomography (PET) device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-PX">PX</a></td><td>Panaromique X-Ray</td><td>Panoramic X-Ray device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-RESP">RESP</a></td><td>Onde respiratoire</td><td/></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-RF">RF</a></td><td>Radio-fluoroscopie</td><td>Radiofluoroscopy device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-RG">RG</a></td><td>Imagerie radiographique</td><td>Radiographic imaging (conventional film/screen)</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-RTIMAGE">RTIMAGE</a></td><td>Image RT</td><td>Radiotherapy Imaging device; includes portal imaging</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-SM">SM</a></td><td>Microscopie à lames</td><td>Slide Microscopy</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-SRF">SRF</a></td><td>Réfraction subjective</td><td>Subjective Refraction device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-TG">TG</a></td><td>Thermographie</td><td>Thermography device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-US">US</a></td><td>Échographie</td><td>Ultrasound device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-VA">VA</a></td><td>Acuité visuelle</td><td>Visual Acuity device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-XA">XA</a></td><td>Angiographie X-Ray</td><td>X-Ray Angiography device</td></tr><tr><td><a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/R4/codesystem-dicom-dcim.html#dicom-dcim-XC">XC</a></td><td>Caméra de photographie externe</td><td>External-camera Photography device</td></tr></table></li></ul></div>
